@startuml
title Token Exchange and Legacy Flow

actor "Client App\n(SiteA)" as SiteA
participant "API Gateway / BFF\n(SiteB)" as SiteB
participant "Resource Server\n(SiteC)" as SiteC
participant "Auth Server\n(TokenServer)" as TokenServer

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

== Modern Flow: OAuth2 Token Exchange ==

group On-Behalf-Of Flow (Token Exchange)
    SiteA -> TokenServer: 1. Request Token A\n(grant_type: client_credentials, scope: api_b)
    activate TokenServer
    TokenServer --> SiteA: Return Token A (for SiteB)
    deactivate TokenServer

    SiteA -> SiteB: 2. Call API with Token A\n(GET /exchange-and-call-c)
    activate SiteB

    SiteB -> TokenServer: 3. Exchange Token A for Token C\n(grant_type: token_exchange, subject_token: Token A, scope: api_c)
    activate TokenServer
    TokenServer --> SiteB: Return Token C (with 'act' claim for SiteA)
    deactivate TokenServer

    SiteB -> SiteC: 4. Call downstream API with Token C\n(GET /data)
    activate SiteC

    alt Introspection (Optional)
        SiteC -> TokenServer: 5a. Validate Token C via introspection\n(POST /connect/introspect)
        activate TokenServer
        TokenServer --> SiteC: Return { active: true, claims: [...] }
        deactivate TokenServer
    else Local Validation (Default)
        SiteC -> SiteC: 5b. Validate Token C signature and claims locally
    end

    SiteC --> SiteB: 6. Return protected data from Site C
    deactivate SiteC

    SiteB --> SiteA: 7. Return final data
    deactivate SiteB
end

... ...

== Legacy Flow: Custom Header & Central Validation ==

group Custom Token Flow
    SiteA -> TokenServer: 1. Request simple token\n(GET /api/simple-token/generate)
    activate TokenServer
    TokenServer --> SiteA: Return { "token": "guid-xyz" }
    deactivate TokenServer

    SiteA -> SiteB: 2. Call API with custom header\n(X-Custom-Auth-Token: guid-xyz)
    activate SiteB

    SiteB -> TokenServer: 3. Validate token centrally\n(POST /api/simple-token/validate)
    activate TokenServer
    TokenServer --> SiteB: Return { "active": true }
    deactivate TokenServer
    
    SiteB -> SiteC: 4. Call downstream API with same custom header
    activate SiteC

    SiteC -> TokenServer: 5. **(Inefficient)** Validate token again centrally
    activate TokenServer
    TokenServer --> SiteC: Return { "active": true }
    deactivate TokenServer
    
    SiteC --> SiteB: 6. Return protected data
    deactivate SiteC
    
    SiteB --> SiteA: 7. Return final data
    deactivate SiteB
end

@enduml